<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- This hymn is notable for staying in minor throughout (Bm as tonic, Em as iv).
  The arrangement treats Bm as the tonal center throughout.
- Bars 1-8 (A section): Light 2-note RH with half-note harmonic rhythm,
  LH 4-note open Bm/F#m/Em voicings.
- Bars 9-13 (B section, higher range): RH shifts to higher register (E5, C#5)
  to track the melody without crowding.
- Bars 14-18 (A' section): Growing texture, climax at bar 18 with full 3-note RH.
  Bar 17 uses Bm7 (pattern "333") for added richness before final Bm.
- Final bar: Bm root position close, both hands light.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bars 2-4: LH voice Em→Bm→F#m→Bm forms a smooth Bm-related progression,
  all minor chords sharing the F# and B common tones.
- Bar 10: LH Bm→A creates a deceptive motion: vi→V in D major flavor.
- Bar 15: ⑦°→① voice leading: LH moves C#°→D cleanly with C# in bass.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Bars 1-4: Sparse 2-note RH, 4-note LH. Open and quiet.
- Bars 5-12: Same density but more movement in RH.
- Bars 13-16: Textural pause at rest bar, then rebuilding.
- Bars 17-19: Fuller 3-note RH, culminating in full Bm close.
-->
